comments: Morris (WAS) makes marginal contact to DeRozan's (CHI) body as he gathers and enters his upward shooting motion during the driving shot attempt. DeRozan is able to move through the contact and finish the play near the rim.
Caruso (CHI) momentarily places a collapsed arm against Beal's (WAS) body during the drive and the contact is marginal.
Caruso (CHI) moves alongside Beal?s (WAS) path and maintains a legal guarding position as incidental contact occurs during the driving shot attempt.
Vucevic (CHI) establishes himself in Beal?s (WAS) path and does not deliver illegal contact.
Beal (WAS) legally contests DeRozan?s (CHI) jump shot attempt.
DeRozan (CHI) does not overtly or abruptly extend his leg out as incidental contact occurs with Beal (WAS) during the jump shot attempt.
The contact between Caruso (CHI) and Morris (WAS) is incidental, and Morris loses his balance reaching backwards for the rebound.
Porzingis (WAS) is positioned inside of the restricted area when contact occurs with DeRozan (CHI) during his driving shot attempt.
Gill (WAS) establishes himself in Caruso?s (CHI) path and does not deliver illegal contact.
DeRozan (CHI) jumps vertically contesting the shot attempt at the basket by Beal (WAS) and is turned mid-air by Beal extending his knee into him.
Vucevic (CHI) establishes himself in Beal?s (WAS) path and does not deliver illegal contact.
Gill (WAS) establishes himself in Caruso?s (CHI) path and does not deliver illegal contact.
Caruso (CHI) moves alongside Beal?s (WAS) path and maintains a legal guarding position as incidental contact occurs during the driving shot attempt.
Gill (WAS) contests DeRozan?s (CHI) jump shot attempt and initiates contact with his foot before DeRozan has returned to the floor.
